To combat these problems, we need philosophy more than ever.  -->

Humans are great at creating tools. But philosophy teaches us <span class="italic font-semibold text-blue-900">when</span> and <span class="italic font-semibold text-blue-900">how</span> to use those tools in just and beneficial ways. 

<span class="italic font-semibold text-blue-900">
    Political philosophy</span> shows us how to organize ourselves.
<span class="italic font-semibold text-blue-900">Ethics</span> guides us in how we ought to treat one another.
<span class="italic font-semibold text-blue-900">Metaphysics</span> teaches us to question the universe.
<span class="italic font-semibold text-blue-900">Existentialism</span> brings us to question our place in it.

Beyond that, thinking like a philosopher trains you to be a problem-solver, a persuasive orator, and a critical thinker. 

Dialexicon is the first step on that journey, beginning with youth.
        </p>
    </div>

